== Rice ==

First you need to prepare your veggies! Peel and chop your @onion{1} into
approximately 1cm pieces and roughly chop your @closed cup mushrooms{1} into
1cm pieces as well. Roughly chop your @coriander{5}.

Put your chopped onion in a large #pot on medium heat with @oil{1%tbsp}. Cook
gently for around ~{5%minutes} until the onion is soft, then add your mushrooms
along with @salt{1/2%tsp} and a good grind of @pepper{} and cook until they
have reduced down (about ~{5%minutes}).

When your onion and mushrooms are nicely cooked, add your @cinnamon & turmeric
spice mix{1%tsp}, and @Panang curry paste{1%tbsp} (use less than 1 tbsp if
you like things less spicy!) and cook for a further ~{2%minutes}, then add your
@basmati rice{2%servings}, @raisins{2%tbsp}, @vegetable stock pot{1} and
@water{800%ml}. Stir everything together and bring to a boil, then reduce the
heat, put your lid on the #pot and allow the rice to simmer for
~{10%minutes} before taking it off the heat and resting it for another
~{10%minutes}.

> Do not peek under the lid for the whole 20 mins!

== Salmon ==

Give your kitchen a quick tidy and then tackle your salmon! Pre-heat your
#grill to high. Put your @apricot and ginger chutney{1%tbsp} in a #bowl with
@water{3%tbsp}, @salt{1/2%tsp} and a good grind of @pepper{} and mix
thoroughly. Coat your @salmon fillet{3} in the chutney mixture, pop them on a
#baking tray{} and grill them for ~{5%minutes} on one side before turning and
grilling them for ~{4%minutes} on the other side.

Once cooked, get the salmon out from under the grill and using a #fork
separate it into flaky pieces.

> If you do this in the baking tray you cooked the salmon in, then you will
also mix the lovely chutney together with the salmon and you also save on
washing up!

== Finishing ==

When the rice is cooked, add half the coriander to the #pot along with the
@baby spinach{3%handfuls}. Stir through, put the lid back on the pot and leave
for ~{2-3%minutes} so the spinach wilts.

Finally, add the salmon to the #pot, stir everything and serve your lovely
rice in #bowls{} with the coriander sprinkled over the top.